race.comment: TENNESSEE BOUND (8) was a dominant winner on debut at Kyneton when backed into a short-priced favourite, sitting on speed and coming right away to win by 2.25 lengths in good time. This looks a suitable progression and with any natural improvement she can make it 2/2. CHERRABAH (9) was okay when sent out at $1.80 first up at Kilmore but has shown ability to date and will strip much fitter. Wary. KING WEST (1) struggled fresh at Hamilton over 1100m but was firmly in the market there in a stronger race won by a good horse. There were post-race excuses offered and he could bounce back quickly here. LADY SADLER (14) resumes, now with the Clinton McDonald yard. She may need a bit further but watch the betting for a gude.
